<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><font style="font-size: 24px;"><b>Installing the Node.js</b></font></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># Version: 10.3</font></div><div><font color="#929292"># Update the Ports Tree</font></div><div>=&gt; <b>cd</b> <font color="#941100">/usr/ports/www/node</font></div><div>=&gt;<font color="#ff40ff"> sudo</font> <b>make install clean</b></div><div><font color="#929292"># The above command  forced me to edit the “/etc/make.conf” and add the line</font><br /></div><div><font color="#929000">DEFAULT_VERSIONS+=ssl=openssl-devel</font></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># Then  run the “make install clean” command again</font></div><div><font color="#929292"># It will install the "openssl-devel-1.1.0” package as a dependency first.</font></div><div><hr /></div><div><font><b><font size="5">In intalling the NPM </font></b></font></div><div><font><b><font style="font-size: 18px;">(Node Package Manager)</font></b></font></div><div><font color="#929292"># Version: npm-5.10.0</font></div><div>=&gt;<b> cd</b><font color="#941100"> /usr/ports/www/npm</font></div><div><br /></div></en-note>